sentences: Crossland made her Wigmore Hall solo debut in 2004.
She recorded in 2003 Bach's English Suite
In 2005, she recorded works by Bach, Handel and Scarlatti on a historic fortepiano, built by Jirikowsky in 1824, at Restoration House in Rochester.

She recorded Parts I and II of the Well-Tempered Clavier, and a reviewer of Gramophone noted in 2008 the "warm, rounded and perpetually singing sonority" of her playing, but also a tendency to give the material profile and character in the beginning of a piece but not follow through to the end.
